# Task 8 – Configure SLA Start / Stop /Pause Conditions

## Project

**Virtual Agent–Driven SLA Breach Awareness & Justification System**

---

## Objective

This task configures the lifecycle conditions of the Incident Resolution SLA to determine when the SLA starts, pauses, stops, and resets during the Incident lifecycle.

---

## Navigation

**Service Level Management → SLA Definitions**

---

## SLA Conditions

| Condition | Configuration |
|-----------|---------------|
| Start | Active = True, State = New or In Progress |
| Pause | State = On Hold |
| Stop | State = Resolved or Closed |
| Reset | None |

---

## Steps Performed

- Opened SLA Definition
- Configured Start Condition
- Configured Pause Condition
- Configured Stop Condition
- Verified Reset Condition
- Updated the SLA

---

## Deliverables

- SLA Lifecycle Configuration
- Start Condition
- Pause Condition
- Stop Condition
- Configuration Screenshots

---

## Expected Result

The SLA automatically starts, pauses, and stops according to the configured Incident states, ensuring accurate SLA calculations and compliance tracking.

---

## Status

**Completed**

